                                "template": "subheader",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "Construction Moves Ahead as First Concrete Pour is Completed"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "content",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "Early in the morning on Sat., Aug. 20, construction crews at Harker’s upper school campus pumped concrete into the footings of what will be the theater at the new Harker performing arts center. “We actually pumped approximately 1 million pounds of concrete over the course of about five hours,” said Mike Bassoni, Harker’s facilities director. The pour was carried out by a truck utilizing a 136-foot boom that stretched nearly the entire length of the construction site."
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "button",
                                "options": {
